      • createCoordinate

        public static java.util.Optional<Coordinate> createCoordinate(Coordinate coordinate,
                                                              Direction direction,
                                                              int factor)
        Instantiates a new Coordinate Object and returns in an Optional Does not throw Exception but returns an Optional.empty if the instantiation fails Does the same as createCoordinate(int x, int y) but adds the offset of the param d and a factor
        Parameters:
        coordinate - coordinate object of the current position
        direction - offset direction at which the new coordinate shall be created
        factor - factor which shall be multiplied whith the offset
        Returns:
        Coordinate object wrapped in an Optional
